   Legal Information About Our Web Site

   TERMS OF USE

      PLEASE READ THESE TERMS OF USE CAREFULLY BEFORE USING THIS WEB SITE.

      By using this site, you signify your assent to these terms of use. If
      you do not agree to them, please do not use the site. User expressly
      acknowledges that use of this site is at user's sole risk.

   Restrictions on Use of Materials

      This site is operated and maintained by the California Energy
      Commission's (referred to as "Commission" herein) Media and Public
      Communications Office. No material or information from this site may be
      copied, reproduced, republished, uploaded, posted, transmitted or
      distributed except as authorized in these terms of use, expressly
      authorized on the information or materials themselves, or approved in
      writing by the Commission.

      Materials and information in this site are provided as a public
      service. Most of these materials and information were generated,
      compiled or assembled at public expense and are freely available for
      public use consistent with the Public Records Act (California
      Government Code section 6250 et. seq.), provided you keep intact all
      copyright, trademark and other proprietary notices and credit the
      Commission when using these materials and information.

      Some of the materials and information in this site, such as the Third
      Party Materials addressed below and select materials bearing a
      copyright notice, may not be used for any purpose. Use or modification
      of these materials or information for commercial or profit making
      purposes is prohibited and may violate the copyrights and/or other
      proprietary rights of the Commission or third parties. Questions
      concerning the use of materials and information in this site should be
      directed to Bob Aldrich, the Commission's Webmaster and Supervisor of
      Web Development, at 916-654-4993 or via e-mail at: boba@energy.ca.gov.

      Access Energy^TM and Energy Quest^TM are trademarks of the California
      Energy Commission. All rights in the use of these marks are reserved by
      the Commission.

      For information about Privacy, please go to our Privacy Policy Page.

   Third Party Materials

      Some materials and information used in the Internet site were generated
      by third parties, who have consented to the Commission's use or
